15/07/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski convened the Council for National Security on Friday (15 July).
Officials say the meeting is in response to recent attacks on the police station in Vratnica and the activities of alleged extremists in Radusa and Kondovo, near Skopje.
In other news, Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski attended the annual assembly of the European Business Association in Skopje on Thursday.
Buckovski said the association has the full support of the government, since it boosts economic development.
Buckovski also pledged that the government would continue efforts to create a better business environment.
(Dnevnik - 15/07/05;
MIA, Tanjug, A1 TV, Macedonian Government Web site - 14/07/05)
